## Project Overview

### What Does This Project Do?

This is a **research project** that implements an **intelligent document retrieval system** optimized for technical documentation (automotive manuals, aerospace docs, engineering schematics). The system is designed to be **faster than existing solutions while maintaining high accuracy**.

**Core Innovation:** Instead of processing all document pages the same way, it uses a **smart router** to classify pages and route them through different processing pipelines:
- **Text-heavy pages** вҶ’ Fast text extraction + embedding (~1-5 seconds)
- **Visual-critical pages** (diagrams, charts) вҶ’ Vision-based embedding (~4 seconds)

**Goal:** Achieve >90% of ColPali's (state-of-the-art vision RAG) accuracy with 50-70% less latency.

### Key Technologies
- **Router:** Microsoft DiT (Document Image Transformer) for page classification
- **Text Path:** PaddleOCR v5 for text extraction + nomic-embed-text for embeddings
- **Vision Path:** ColPali (vision-based document understanding)
- **Vector DB:** Qdrant or LanceDB for storing embeddings
- **Hardware:** Optimized for Apple Silicon (M1/M2/M3) with MPS backend

---

## The Problem Being Solved

### Traditional Approaches Have Limitations

**Approach 1: OCR-based RAG (Traditional)**
- вң… Fast text extraction
- вқҢ **"Diagram Blindness"** - Loses spatial information in charts, diagrams, schematics
- вқҢ Fails on visual-heavy technical documents

**Approach 2: Vision RAG (ColPali - Current SOTA)**
- вң… Excellent accuracy on all document types
- вң… Preserves spatial/visual information
- вқҢ **Computationally expensive** (~1,000 embeddings per page)
- вқҢ ~4 seconds per page on M1 Pro

### Our Solution: Adaptive Hybrid Approach

**Key Insight:** Not all pages need expensive vision processing!

- **Text-heavy pages** (70% of technical docs): Use fast OCR path
- **Visual-critical pages** (diagrams, charts): Use vision path

This achieves the **best of both worlds**:
- Fast processing for simple pages
- Accurate processing for complex visual content
- Overall 50-70% speedup while maintaining >90% accuracy

